 Ōöé\n267:               Ō¢╝\n268: ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n269: Ōöé Determine Endpoint          Ōöé\n270: Ōöé - agentcube: router_url     Ōöé\n271: Ōöé - k8s: node_port service    Ōöé\n272: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n273:               Ōöé\n274:               Ōö£ŌöĆ provider=agentcube ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢║ POST to AgentRuntime\n275:               Ōöé                          - /v1/namespaces/{ns}/\n276:               Ōöé                            agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/\n277:               Ōöé                          - Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id header\n278:               Ōöé\n279:               ŌööŌöĆ provider=k8s ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢║ POST to Service endpoint\n280:                                          - http://localhost:{node_port}\n281:                                          - Direct HTTP invocation\n282:               Ōöé\n283:               Ō¢╝\n284:         Return Response\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ## Interface\n290: \n291: ### Console Script Entry Point\n292: \n293: ```toml\n294: [project.scripts]\n295: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### Global CLI Options\n299: \n300: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n301: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n302: | `--version` | bool | None | Show version and exit (eager option) |\n303: | `--verbose` / `-v` | bool | False | Enable verbose output with DEBUG logging |\n304: \n305: ### Pack Command\n306: \n307: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n308: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n309: | `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n310: | `--agent-name` | str | None | Override the agent name |\n311: | `--language` | str | None | Programming language (python, java) |\n312: | `--entrypoint` | str | None | Override the entrypoint command |\n313: | `--port` | int | None | Port to expose in Dockerfile |\n314: | `--build-mode` | str | None | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n315: | `--description` | str | None | Agent description |\n316: | `--output` | str | None | Output path for packaged workspace |\n317: | `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n318: \n319: ### Build Command\n320: \n321: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n322: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n323: | `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n324: | `-p`, `--proxy` | str | None | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n325: | `--cloud-provider` | str | None | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n326: | `--output` | str | None | Output path for build artifacts |\n327: | `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n328: \n329: ### Publish Command\n330: \n331: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n332: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n333: | `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n334: | `--version` | str | None | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n335: | `--image-url` | str | None | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n336: | `--image-username` | str | None | Username for image repository |\n337: | `--image-password` | str | None | Password for image repository |\n338: | `--description` | str | None | Agent description |\n339: | `--region` | str | None | Deployment region |\n340: | `--cloud-provider` | str | None | Cloud provider name |\n341: | `--provider` | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n342: | `--node-port` | int | None | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n343: | `--replicas` | int | None | Number of replicas for K8s deployment |\n344: | `--namespace` | str | None | Namespace for deployment |\n345: | `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n346: \n347: ### Invoke Command\n348: \n349: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n350: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n351: | `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n352: | `--payload` | str | \"{}\" | JSON-formatted input passed to agent |\n353: | `--header` | List[str] | None | Custom HTTP headers (repeatable) |\n354: | `--provider` | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n355: | `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n356: \n357: ### Status Command\n358: \n359: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n360: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n361: | `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n362: | `--provider` | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n363: | `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: ## Data Models\n368: \n369: ### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n370: \n371: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n372: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n373: | `agent_name` | str | required | Unique name identifying the agent |\n374: | `description` | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n375: | `language` | str | \"python\" | Programming language (python/java) |\n376: | `entrypoint` | str | required | Command to launch the agent |\n377: | `port` | int | 8080 | Port exposed by agent runtime |\n378: | `build_mode` | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n379: | `region` | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n380: | `version` | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version for publishing |\n381: | `image` | Optional[Dict] | None | Container image information |\n382: | `auth` | Optional[Dict] | None | Authentication configuration |\n383: | `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n384: | `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry URL for image publishing |\n385: | `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry username |\n386: | `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry password |\n387: | `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | None | Agent endpoint URL |\n388: | `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for Workload Manager |\n389: | `router_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for Router |\n390: | `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | None | Path for readiness probe |\n391: | `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | None | Port for readiness probe |\n392: | `agent_id` | Optional[str] | None | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n393: | `session_id` | Optional[str] | None | Session ID for the agent |\n394: | `k8s_deployment` | Optional[Dict] | None | Kubernetes deployment information |\n395: \n396: **Validators:**\n397: - `validate_language` ŌåÆ lowercase, must be 'python' or 'java'\n398: - `validate_build_mode` ŌåÆ lowercase, must be 'local' or 'cloud'\n399: - `validate_port` ŌåÆ must be 1..65535\n400: \n401: ### MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n402: \n403: | Field | Type | Default |\n404: |-------|------|---------|\n405: | `agent_name` | Optional[str] | None |\n406: | `language` | Optional[str] | 'python' |\n407: | `entrypoint` | Optional[str] | None |\n408: | `port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n409: | `build_mode` | Optional[str] | 'local' |\n410: | `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | None |\n411: | `description` | Optional[str] | None |\n412: | `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n413: | `router_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n414: | `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n415: | `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n416: | `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n417: | `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n418: | `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n419: | `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ## Error Handling\n424: \n425: ### Error Patterns\n426: \n427: | Error | Description | Handling |\n428: |-------|-------------|----------|\n429: | `ValueError` | Invalid input, missing required fields | Print in red, exit code 1 |\n430: | `RuntimeError` | Docker/K8s operation failures | Print in red, exit code 1 |\n431: | `FileNotFoundError` | Missing workspace/metadata files | Print guidance, exit code 1 |\n432: | `ValidationError` | Pydantic validation failures | Print field errors, exit code 1 |\n433: | `ConnectionError` | Network/registry failures | Print with retry suggestion, exit code 1 |\n434: | `TimeoutError` | K8s deployment readiness timeout | Print timeout message, exit code 1 |\n435: \n436: ### Error Handler Function\n437: \n438: ```python\n439: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n440:     \"\"\"Print error and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n441:     # Print \"Error {command_name}: {e}\" in red\n442:     # If verbose, print full traceback\n443:     # raise typer.Exit(1)\n444: ```\n445: \n446: ### Exit Codes\n447: \n448: | Exit Code | Meaning |\n449: |-----------|---------|\n450: | 0 | Success |\n451: | 1 | General error (validation, runtime) |\n452: | 2 | Missing dependencies (Docker, K8s) |\n453: | 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ## Security Considerations\n458: \n459: ### Sensitive Data Handling\n460: \n461: | Data | Storage | Transmission |\n462: |------|---------|--------------|\n463: | Registry passwords | Environment variables only | HTTPS with TLS |\n464: | Kubernetes tokens | kubeconfig or in-cluster SA | mTLS when available |\n465: | Agent session IDs | Local metadata file | Header encryption |\n466: | Image pull secrets | Kubernetes secrets | Cluster-internal only |\n467: \n468: ### RBAC Requirements (for Kubernetes Provider)\n469: \n470: | Resource | Verbs |\n471: |----------|-------|\n472: | `deployments` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n473: | `services` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n474: | `agentruntimes` (CR) | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n475: | `pods` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n476: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `create`, `update` |\n477: \n478: ### Dockerfile Security\n479: \n480: - Use official base images (python:3.x-slim, openjdk:xx-jre-slim)\n481: - Run as non-root user where possible\n482: - Pin package versions in requirements.txt\n483: - Minimize layer count\n484: - Scan images before publishing (out of scope, recommended)\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## Impact Analysis\n489: \n490: ### Files Created\n491: \n492: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n493: |------|--------------|-------------|\n494: | `pyproject.toml` | ~80 | Package metadata and dependencies |\n495: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | ~30 | Package exports |\n496: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | ~10 | CLI subpackage marker |\n497: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | ~350 | Main CLI with all commands |\n498: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | ~60 | MetadataOptions dataclass |\n499: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | ~20 | Runtime re-exports |\n500: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | ~280 | PackRuntime implementation |\n501: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | ~200 | BuildRuntime implementation |\n502: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | ~250 | PublishRuntime implementation |\n503: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | ~180 | InvokeRuntime implementation |\n504: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | ~120 | StatusRuntime implementation |\n505: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | ~15 | Services package docstring |\n506: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | ~180 | AgentMetadata and MetadataService |\n507: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | ~220 | Docker SDK wrapper |\n508: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | ~200 | Kubernetes Deployment/Service provider |\n509: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | ~180 | AgentRuntime CR provider |\n510: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | ~10 | Operations placeholder |\n511: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | ~40 | Example agent |\n512: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | ~60 | Example math agent |\n513: | **Total** | **~2,715** | |\n514: \n515: ### Dependencies\n516: \n517: ```toml\n518: [project]\n519: dependencies = [\n520:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n521:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n522:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n523:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n524:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n525:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n526:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n527:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n528:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n529: ]\n530: \n531: [project.optional-dependencies]\n532: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n533: dev = [\n534:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n535:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n536:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n537:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n538:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n539:     \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n540:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n541: ]\n542: test = [\n543:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n544:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n545:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n546:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n547:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n548: ]\n549: ```\n550: \n551: ### Downstream Consumers\n552: \n553: | Consumer | Usage |\n554: |----------|-------|\n555: | Agent Developers | Package, build, publish agents locally |\n556: | CI/CD Pipelines | Automated agent builds and deployments |\n557: | Helm Charts | Pre-deployment validation and packaging |\n558: | Documentation | Example commands and workflows |\n559: \n560: ### Performance Characteristics\n561: \n562: | Operation | Time (est.) | Notes |\n563: |-----------|-------------|-------|\n564: | `pack` | <1s | Workspace validation and Dockerfile generation |\n565: | `build` (local) | 30s-5min | Depends on image size and network |\n566: | `build` (cloud) | 2-10min | Depends on cloud provider queue |\n567: | `publish` (k8s) | 30s-2min | Image push + deployment rollout |\n568: | `publish` (agentcube) | 10s-1min | CR creation + readiness check |\n569: | `invoke` | <100ms | HTTP request to running agent |\n570: | `status` | <1s | K8s API query |\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ## Alternatives Considered\n575: \n576: ### Alternative 1: Pure Go CLI\n577: \n578: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n579: |--------|------------|\n580: | **Pros** | Single language codebase; smaller binary; faster startup; easier cross-compilation |\n581: | **Cons** | Docker SDK less mature in Go; more boilerplate; steeper learning curve for Python developers; Kubernetes SDK more verbose |\n582: | **Decision** | **Rejected** ŌĆö Python offers better ecosystem for CLI tooling (Typer/Rich), more mature Docker SDK, easier scripting integration |\n583: \n584: ### Alternative 2: Separate CLIs per Command\n585: \n586: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n587: |--------|------------|\n588: | **Pros** | Smaller individual binaries; independent versioning; focused scope |\n589: | **Cons** | Duplicated code; more packages to maintain; inconsistent UX; harder to discover |\n590: | **Decision** | **Rejected** ŌĆö Unified CLI provides better developer experience, shared code, consistent patterns |\n591: \n592: ### Alternative 3: kubectl Plugin Architecture\n593: \n594: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n595: |--------|------------|\n596: | **Pros** | Native kubectl integration; familiar to K8s users; leverages kubectl config |\n597: | **Cons** | Requires kubectl installation; limited to K8s workflows; harder to implement non-K8s features |\n598: | **Decision** | **Rejected** ŌĆö Standalone CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides more flexibility, works without kubectl for local development |\n599: \n600: ### Alternative 4: Web-Based Dashboard\n601: \n602: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n603: |--------|------------|\n604: | **Pros** | Rich UI; visual feedback; easier for beginners; no local installation |\n605: | **Cons** | Requires backend service; network dependency; harder to script; more complex architecture |\n606: | **Decision** | **Rejected** ŌĆö CLI is prerequisite for automation and CI/CD; web UI can be added later as separate component |\n607: \n608: ---\n609: \n610: ## Risks and Mitigations\n611: \n612: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n613: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n614: | Docker SDK compatibility issues | Medium | Medium | Pin docker>=6.0.0; test on multiple Docker versions |\n615: | Kubernetes SDK authentication edge cases | Medium | High | Support kubeconfig, in-cluster, and env-based auth; clear error messages |\n616: | Cross-platform path handling | Medium | Medium | Use `pathlib.Path` consistently; test on Windows/Linux/macOS |\n617: | Metadata format evolution | Medium | Medium | Pydantic validators; migration utilities; version field in metadata |\n618: | Python version compatibility | Low | Medium | Require Python>=3.10; test matrix in CI |\n619: | Large workspace packaging | Medium | Low | .dockerignore support; size warnings; exclude patterns |\n620: | Registry authentication failures | Medium | High | Retry with exponential backoff; clear credential prompts |\n621: | Concurrent metadata modifications | Low | Medium | File locking or atomic writes; last-write-wins with warnings |\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## Verification\n626: \n627: ### Installation Verification\n628: \n629: ```bash\n630: # Install the CLI\n631: pip install -e ./cmd/cli\n632: \n633: # Verify entry point\n634: which kubectl-agentcube\n635: kubectl-agentcube --version\n636: ```\n637: \n638: ### Pack Command Verification\n639: \n640: ```bash\n641: # Create test workspace\n642: mkdir -p /tmp/test-agent\n643: cat > /tmp/test-agent/main.py << 'EOF'\n644: from flask import Flask\n645: app = Flask(__name__)\n646: \n647: @app.route('/invoke', methods=['POST'])\n648: def invoke():\n649:     return {\"message\": \"Hello from agent\"}\n650: \n651: if __name__ == '__main__':\n652:     app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=8080)\n653: EOF\n654: \n655: # Pack the agent\n656: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent --language python\n657: \n658: # Verify metadata created\n659: ls /tmp/test-agent/agent_metadata.yaml\n660: ls /tmp/test-agent/Dockerfile\n661: ```\n662: \n663: ### Build Command Verification\n664: \n665: ```bash\n666: # Build the agent (requires Docker)\n667: kubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose\n668: \n669: # Verify Docker image\n670: docker images | grep test-agent\n671: ```\n672: \n673: ### Publish Command Verification (requires K8s)\n674: \n675: ```bash\n676: # Publish to Kubernetes\n677: kubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n678:   --provider k8s \\\n679:   --namespace default \\\n680:   --image-url myregistry/test-agent:latest\n681: \n682: # Verify deployment\n683: kubectl get deployment test-agent\n684: kubectl get service test-agent\n685: ```\n686: \n687: ### Invoke Command Verification\n688: \n689: ```bash\n690: # Invoke the agent\n691: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n692:   --payload '{\"input\": \"hello\"}' \\\n693:   --provider k8s\n694: ```\n695: \n696: ### Status Command Verification\n697: \n698: ```bash\n699: # Check status\n700: kubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s\n701: ```\n702: \n703: ### Error Handling Verification\n704: \n705: ```bash\n706: # Test missing workspace\n707: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /nonexistent 2>&1 | grep -q \"Error\" && echo \"Error handling works\"\n708: \n709: # Test invalid JSON payload\n710: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent --payload 'invalid json' 2>&1 | grep -q \"JSON\" && echo \"JSON validation works\"\n711: \n712: # Test verbose mode\n713: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose 2>&1 | grep -q \"DEBUG\" && echo \"Verbose mode works\"\n714: ```\n715: \n716: ---\n717: \n718: ## References\n719: \n720: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) ŌĆö Detailed design specifications\n721: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) ŌĆö Complete requirements specification\n722: - [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) ŌĆö Python SDK for programmatic access\n723: - [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) ŌĆö Kubernetes client patterns\n724: - [project.md](project.md) ŌĆö Project context and architecture\n725: \n726: ---\n727: \n728: ## Success Criteria\n729: \n730: 1. Ō£ģ All 5 CLI commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`) are implemented\n731: 2. Ō£ģ Typer app initializes with proper help text and version display\n732: 3. Ō£ģ Global `--verbose` flag enables DEBUG logging\n733: 4. Ō£ģ `pack` validates workspace structure and generates Dockerfile\n734: 5. Ō£ģ `pack` creates/updates `agent_metadata.yaml` with Pydantic validation\n735: 6. Ō£ģ `build` supports both local Docker and cloud build modes\n736: 7. Ō£ģ `publish` supports both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment) providers\n737: 8. Ō£ģ `invoke` correctly POSTs JSON payload and handles session headers\n738: 9. Ō£ģ `status` displays Rich Table with deployment information\n739: 10. Ō£ģ All commands use consistent error handling with `_handle_error`\n740: 11. Ō£ģ Metadata loading falls back through `agent_metadata.yaml` ŌåÆ `agent.yaml` ŌåÆ `metadata.yaml`\n741: 12. Ō£ģ Python and Java language support with appropriate Dockerfile templates\n742: 13. Ō£ģ Docker image operations work with registry authentication\n743: 14. Ō£ģ Kubernetes provider creates Deployment + NodePort Service correctly\n744: 15. Ō£ģ AgentCube provider creates AgentRuntime CR with proper spec\n745: 16. Ō£ģ All runtime classes follow spec: `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`\n746: 17. Ō£ģ Services layer properly abstracted: `MetadataService`, `DockerService`, `KubernetesProvider`, `AgentCubeProvider`\n747: 18. Ō£ģ Package structure follows spec with proper `__init__.py` exports\n748: 19. Ō£ģ `kubectl-agentcube` console script entry point works after pip install\n749: 20. Ō£ģ Examples directory contains working `hello-agent` and `math-agent`\n750: \n751: ---\n752: \n753: *AR-020 ŌĆö Module: cmd/cli ŌĆö Language: Python ŌĆö Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 753 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AgentCube CLI Toolkit (kubectl-agentcube)\n\n## AR-020 ŌĆö CLI pack ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a comprehensive command-line interface (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **`pack`** ŌĆö Validates and prepares agent workspace, generates Dockerfiles, manages metadata\n2. **`build`** ŌĆö Builds container images from packaged workspaces (local Docker or cloud builds)\n3. **`publish`** ŌĆö Publishes/deploys agents to AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886494875,"end":1775886494893}}}}
