{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886588294,"sessionID":"ses_284ebb1d0ffeBv9YVKRFhZV4Mg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b159102001sCl7W4crS45Fbk","messageID":"msg_d7b156cdf001ca3teazNuVYWuH","sessionID":"ses_284ebb1d0ffeBv9YVKRFhZV4Mg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: CLI Build Command (AR-021)\n\n## AR-021 ŌĆö CLI build ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to enable developers to build container images from packaged agent workspaces. The build command is a critical component of the agent lifecycle management workflow, bridging the gap between workspace packaging (`pack`) and deployment/publishing (`publish`).\n\nThe build command SHALL:\n- Build container images from packaged agent workspaces using Docker\n- Support both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds\n- Handle version incrementation automatically during the build process\n- Provide proxy configuration for dependency resolution in restricted network environments\n- Integrate seamlessly with the existing `pack` and `publish` commands\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **CLI Command Implementation**\n   - Add `build` subcommand to the Typer CLI application\n   - Command options:\n     - `workspace` (`-f`, `--workspace`): Path to agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n     - `proxy` (`-p`, `--proxy`): Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n     - `cloud_provider` (`--cloud-provider`): Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n     - `output` (`--output`): Output path for build artifacts\n     - `verbose` (`--verbose`): Enable detailed logging\n\n2. **BuildRuntime Implementation**\n   - `BuildRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n   - Core methods:\n     - `build(workspace_path, **options)`: Main build orchestration\n     - `_validate_build_prerequisites()`: Verify Docker availability and workspace state\n     - `_build_local()`: Execute local Docker builds\n     - `_build_cloud()`: Execute cloud-based builds\n     - `_increment_version()`: Automatic version bumping (patch level)\n     - `_update_build_metadata()`: Persist build results to metadata\n\n3. **Docker Integration**\n   - Leverage existing `DockerService` for image building\n   - Support build arguments (e.g., proxy settings)\n   - Tag images with version-derived tags\n   - Return build metadata (image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time)\n\n4. **Version Management**\n   - Automatic version increment on successful build:\n     - Semantic versioning: patch bump for `X.Y.Z` ŌåÆ `X.Y.Z+1`\n     - Fallback: append `.1` for non-semver versions\n     - Fallback: `{version}-1` for edge cases\n   - Version rollback on build failure to maintain consistency\n\n5. **Error Handling**\n   - Docker unavailability detection with clear error messaging\n   - Build failure handling with verbose traceback support\n   - Integration with `_handle_error()` for consistent CLI error patterns\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **Image Publishing**: Handled by the `publish` command\n2. **Registry Authentication**: Managed during `publish` phase\n3. **Multi-platform Builds**: Single-platform builds only (current iteration)\n4. **Build Caching Optimization**: Standard Docker caching behavior\n5. **Custom Build Drivers**: Only Docker daemon-based builds\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Build Command Flow\n\n```\nbuild(workspace, options)\n    Ōöé\n    Ō¢╝\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé Load Metadata               Ōöé\nŌöé - Read agent_metadata.yaml  Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n              Ōöé\n              Ō¢╝\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé Validate Prerequisites      Ōöé\nŌöé - Docker available?         Ōöé\nŌöé - Metadata has image info?  Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n              Ōöé\n              Ō¢╝\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé Increment Version           Ōöé\nŌöé - Patch bump (X.Y.Z ŌåÆ X.Y.Z+1)\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n              Ōöé\n              Ōö£ŌöĆ local ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢║ Build with Docker SDK\n              Ōöé                   - Tag: agent_name:version\n              Ōöé                   - Build context: workspace\n              Ōöé                   - Proxy args if provided\n              Ōöé\n              ŌööŌöĆ cloud ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢║ Cloud provider build API\n                                  - Submit build job\n                                  - Wait for completion\n              Ōöé\n              Ō¢╝\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé Update Build Metadata       Ōöé\nŌöé - Record build info, tag    Ōöé\nŌöé - Save agent_metadata.yaml  Ōöé\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n              Ōöé\n              Ō¢╝\n        Return Result\n```\n\n### BuildRuntime Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    \n    def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Main entry point for building container images.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n    \"\"\"Increment version (patch bump) and return new version.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Verify Docker is available and workspace is ready.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Execute local Docker build.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Execute cloud-based build.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Persist build results to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### Typer Build Command Signature\n\n```python\ndef build(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Command Options Reference\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--proxy` | `-p` | str | None | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n| `--cloud-provider` | | str | None | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--output` | | str | None | Output path for build artifacts |\n| `--verbose` | | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Build Mode Resolution\n\n1. Read `build_mode` from metadata (default: \"local\")\n2. Local builds use `DockerService.build_image()`\n3. Cloud builds delegate to provider-specific implementations\n\n### Version Increment Logic\n\n```python\ndef increment_version(current_version: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Increment version following these rules:\n    - X.Y.Z (semver) ŌåÆ bump patch (X.Y.Z+1)\n    - version with dots ŌåÆ append .1\n    - other ŌåÆ {version}-1\n    \"\"\"\n    if matches_semver(current_version):\n        return bump_patch(current_version)\n    elif '.' in current_version:\n        return f\"{current_version}.1\"\n    else:\n        return f\"{current_version}-1\"\n```\n\n### Local Build Process\n\n```python\ndef _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    # 1. Prepare build arguments (proxy settings)\n    build_args = {}\n    if options.get('proxy'):\n        build_args['HTTP_PROXY'] = options['proxy']\n        build_args['HTTPS_PROXY'] = options['proxy']\n    \n    # 2. Locate Dockerfile\n    dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n    \n    # 3. Build image using DockerService\n    image_name = metadata.agent_name\n    tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n    \n    result = docker_service.build_image(\n        dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n        context_path=workspace_path,\n        image_name=image_name,\n        tag=tag,\n        build_args=build_args if build_args else None\n    )\n    \n    # 4. Return build result with metadata\n    return {\n        \"image_name\": result[\"image_name\"],\n        \"image_id\": result[\"image_id\"],\n        \"image_size\": result[\"image_size\"],\n        \"build_time\": result[\"build_time\"],\n        \"tag\": tag\n    }\n```\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\nAll build errors SHALL propagate through `_handle_error()`:\n- Non-verbose: Print concise error message in red\n- Verbose: Print full traceback\n- Exit code: 1 on any build failure\n\n**Specific Error Cases:**\n\n| Error | Condition | Handling |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| `RuntimeError` | Docker unavailable | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n| `ValueError` | Missing metadata | \"Metadata not found, run 'pack' first\" |\n| `RuntimeError` | Build failure | Print build logs, revert version |\n| `ConnectionError` | Cloud build API | Retry with backoff, clear error message |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact Level | Description |\n|-----------|--------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | High | New `build` command registration and option handling |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | High | New runtime class implementation (~200 lines) |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Medium | Export `BuildRuntime` class |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Low | Add `BuildRuntime` to exports |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Low | Reuse existing `build_image()` method |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Low | Metadata read/write for version tracking |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n**Required:**\n- `pack` command must be executed before `build` (validated via metadata)\n- `DockerService` must be functional for local builds\n- `AgentMetadata` model for version and configuration storage\n\n**Dependent:**\n- `publish` command depends on successful `build` output\n- Status tracking depends on build metadata\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Docker daemon unavailable | Medium | High | Clear error message; validate prerequisites early |\n| Version increment conflicts | Low | Medium | Atomic metadata updates; rollback on failure |\n| Cloud provider API failures | Low | High | Fallback to local build; clear error reporting |\n| Large workspace build timeouts | Medium | Medium | Document timeout limits; support for build args |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Time (est.) | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| `build` (local) | 30s-5min | Depends on image size and network |\n| `build` (cloud) | 2-10min | Depends on cloud provider queue |\n| Version increment | <10ms | File I/O only |\n| Metadata update | <100ms | YAML serialization |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Integrated Pack+Build Command\n\n**Approach:** Combine `pack` and `build` into a single `prepare` command.\n\n**Rejected:** Keeps concerns separatedŌĆöpacking prepares the workspace structure while building creates the container image. Users may want to pack without building (e.g., to review Dockerfile), and the separation enables better error isolation.\n\n### Alternative 2: External Build Tool Integration\n\n**Approach:** Delegate builds to external tools like `kaniko`, `buildah`, or cloud-native buildpacks.\n\n**Rejected:** Adds external dependencies and complexity. The Docker SDK provides sufficient functionality for the initial release. Future iterations may add pluggable build backends.\n\n### Alternative 3: Manual Version Management\n\n**Approach:** Require users to manually update version before each build.\n\n**Rejected:** Error-prone and friction-heavy. Automatic version increment ensures consistent versioning while preserving the ability to override via `agent_metadata.yaml`.\n\n### Alternative 4: Build Cache Externalization\n\n**Approach:** Support external build cache backends (S3, registry).\n\n**Rejected:** Increases complexity without clear benefit for initial use cases. Can be added later if build performance becomes a bottleneck.\n\n### Alternative 5: Buildkit-Only Builds\n\n**Approach:** Require BuildKit for all builds to enable advanced features.\n\n**Rejected:** Not all environments have BuildKit enabled. Standard Docker builds provide broader compatibility.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Build Command Verification (Local)\n\n```bash\n# Prerequisite: pack command has been executed\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent\n\n# Build the agent (requires Docker)\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose\n\n# Verify Docker image was created\ndocker images | grep test-agent\n\n# Verify metadata was updated with build info\ncat /tmp/test-agent/agent_metadata.yaml | grep -A5 \"image\"\n```\n\n### Build with Proxy Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build with proxy configuration\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --proxy http://proxy.company.com:8080 \\\n  --verbose\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```bash\n# Test Docker unavailable (simulated)\n# Should produce: \"Error build: Docker is not available or not running\"\n\n# Test missing metadata\nrm /tmp/test-agent/agent_metadata.yaml\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent 2>&1 | grep -q \"metadata\" && echo \"Error handling works\"\n\n# Test verbose mode\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose 2>&1 | grep -q \"Building\" && echo \"Verbose mode works\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) ŌĆö Detailed CLI design specifications\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) ŌĆö Complete requirements specification\n- AR-020 ŌĆö CLI Pack Command ŌĆö Predecessor command in lifecycle\n- AR-022 ŌĆö CLI Publish Command ŌĆö Successor command in lifecycle\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. Ō£ģ `build` command is registered in Typer CLI with all specified options\n2. Ō£ģ `BuildRuntime` class implements all required methods per spec\n3. Ō£ģ Local Docker builds work with `DockerService.build_image()`\n4. Ō£ģ Cloud builds delegate to appropriate provider APIs\n5. Ō£ģ Version is automatically incremented on successful builds (patch bump)\n6. Ō£ģ Version is rolled back on build failures to maintain consistency\n7. Ō£ģ Docker unavailability produces clear error: \"Docker is not available or not running\"\n8. Ō£ģ Build metadata (image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time) is persisted to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n9. Ō£ģ Proxy settings are passed as build arguments when specified\n10. Ō£ģ All errors use consistent `_handle_error()` pattern with exit code 1\n11. Ō£ģ Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging and full tracebacks\n12. Ō£ģ Command integrates with existing CLI structure and styling\n\n---\n\n*AR-021 ŌĆö Module: cmd/cli ŌĆö Language: Python ŌĆö Size: M*\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886588184,"end":1775886588290}}}}
